properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a severe thunderstorm capable of producing quarter-sized hail and wind gusts in excess of 90 km/h. At 2:33 AM CDT Doppler RADAR indicated that this severe thunderstorm was located over Pelican Lake southeast of Ninette and was moving toward the east at 30 km/h. ### Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Strong wind gusts can toss loose objects, damage weak buildings, break branches off trees and overturn large vehicles.
Expires: 2020-07-13T10:19:33-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2020-07-13T07:36:33-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.1501087888.2020
Area: Mun. of Killarney-Turtle Mountain, R.M. of Argyle incl. Baldur Glenora and Greenway, Cartwright-Roblin Mun. incl. Mather, R.M. of Prairie Lakes incl. Margaret Ninette and Belmont

properties.Title: Fog Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Dense fog is expected to develop tonight and dissipate Monday. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Fog advisories are issued when near zero visibilities in fog are expected or occurring. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.
